<hr>

<h1>BROWSING THE SITE</h1>

<p>The <em>Browse</em> button at has a dropdown menu with a number of ways you can browse the fics. Using the tags on each post you can browse by:</p>

<ul>
    <li>by Author</li>
    <li>by Website</li>
        <ul>
            <li>AO3 (archiveofourown)</li>
            <li>FFn (fanfiction.net)</li>
            <li>LJ (LiveJournal)</li>
            <li>P&amp;P (Passion & Perfection)</li>
        </ul>
</ul>

<p>There are some fics that where posted to other sites, but you can find them by searching <em>authors</em> or by using the URL <code>randommirandyfics.tumblr.com/tagged/[title-of-the-fic]</code> (replace spaces with dashes).</p>

<ul>
    <li>The length of the fic
        <ul>
            <li>Quick Fics (1 - 2 chapters)</li>
            <li>Medium (3 - 9 chapters)</li>
            <li>Longer (10 - 20 chapters)</li>
            <li>Novel (21 + chaperts)</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Completed fics.</li>
    <li>Search by <a href="http://randommirandyfics.tumblr.com/tagged/wip">WIPs</a> is not listed solely because this theme only allows ten links to be added to the dropdown menu.</li>
</ul>

<p>They are set-up this way because these are the ways I usually search for something to re-read. If you have suggestions for better organizing the fics, let me know.</p>

<hr>
<h3>WHAT ABOUT…</h3>

<p>In this dropdown menu you will find almost everything else: credit for the blog’s avatart and background image, received prompts. recommendations, and named fics. You will also find a couple of links to the ask page and a link for submitting a fic.</p>

<hr>
<h3>DISQUS</h3>

<p>This feature has been removed as no one was using it.</p>

<hr>
<h3>Why make the blog?</h3>

<p>This blog gives me a way to remember what I have already read, find when I wanna read it again, and make my slight obsession with Mirandy fairly productive.</p>

<h5>|_・)</h5>

<p>There are two reasons most of the stories I have read are from ffn and ao3: 1) I can easily read both sites on my iPhone and 2) I can navigate both sites to find authors and stories I haven’t read yet. I’m human, and sometimes I just go for easy.<br/><br/>It really is <em>Random</em> Mirandy Fics.</p>

<hr>
<h2>Want more Mirandy?</h2>

<p>For a more comprehensive list of Mirandy fics, please check out the awesome list from XV, over at the <a href="http://uk.groups.yahoo.com/group/DWP_femslash_fanfic/" target="_blank">Yahoo! Mirandy Group</a>. As already stated: XV has made a (searchable) spreadsheet listing virtually every Mirandy fic written.</p>
<p>Or you can check out <a href="http://ao3feed-mirandy.tumblr.com/" target="_blank">AO3 Mirandy Feed</a>. It is a rss/feed blog that does just that; however, it only lists fics posted to Archive of Our Own (aka ao3).</p>

